race.comment: SHEZASEER (6) has been in work a while, stopping and starting at the trials since June. Her latest performance was very strong and the blinkers go on first time today. The inside draw should give her every chance and if she runs up to her latest trial, she'll be hard to hold out. MEMPHIS MINX (10) has disappointed in stronger company in her past couple and has since joined the Martin barn. Her recent trial was solid at Belmont and if she can navigate the tricky barrier, she'll make her presence felt. EL ALAMEIN (7) may have been hindered by wet tracks in recent races and now gets on top of the ground back in grade. The form out of his latest effort has been very strong and it wouldn't surprise to see him turn his form around today. OCTOBER ROX (5) was sound on debut and gets the blinkers on now up in trip. Can feature. GREY REVOLUTION (12) is next best.
